Cell["\<\
Even though I can still copy a SummaryBox with a red icon, it\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]s already a modified object. It\[CloseCurlyQuote]s just \
that its display in Mathematica\[CloseCurlyQuote]s UI is static, and copying \
a SummaryBox with a red icon to the clipboard will keep it that way, but the \
object in memory will not. After all, the SummaryBox is just a display in \
Notepad, and behind the screen is actually just an expression like this:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.912921755028632*^9},ExpressionUUID->"ad1b85d5-715e-44b4-8fc0-\
69b7730f60f9"],

