Cell["\<\
That is, in the example above, the pattern matches the exact value, not \
values of any type. Even taking into account that in all three cases I passed \
a string as the second argument.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.912922495195483*^9},ExpressionUUID->"fd56cb72-fa81-45ca-bac2-\
c44b2e88a913"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Overriding", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.9129225097795773`*^9},ExpressionUUID->"20ee498c-e8c9-42c3-ad2d-\
b68f903b66dd"],

Cell["\<\
We\[CloseCurlyQuote]ve dealt with overloading, although it\[CloseCurlyQuote]s \
only a small part of the possibilities. But what about overriding? That is, \
is it possible to create a function-method with behavior different from the \
same method of its parent? As usual, the answer is yes. Otherwise I wouldn\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]t have written about it. Overriding is also pretty obvious, \
especially after I demonstrated above that you can override default values in \
descendant types. I.e. if we created a descendant and its parent has some \
method that was inherited - we can just override it head-on:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.912922519269846*^9},ExpressionUUID->"29208c0b-b7e4-4348-8fc2-\
3ea981947288"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"CreateType", "[", 
   RowBox[{"Student", ",", "Human", ",", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{"\"\<Course\>\"", "->", "1"}], "}"}]}], "]"}], 
  "\n"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"Student", "/:", 
   RowBox[{"getName", "[", 
    RowBox[{"student_Student", ",", "\"\<last\>\""}], "]"}], ":=", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
    "StringTemplate", "[", "\"\<Call me just `1`. Let's not be formal.\>\"", 
     "]"}], "[", 
    RowBox[{"getName", "[", 
     RowBox[{"student", ",", "\"\<first\>\""}], "]"}], "]"}]}], 
  "\n"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{"Ivan", "=", 
  RowBox[{"Student", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<Name\>\"", "->", "\"\<Ivan\>\""}], "]"}]}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"getName", "[", 
  RowBox[{"Ivan", ",", "\"\<first\>\""}], "]"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"getName", "[", 
  RowBox[{"Ivan", ",", "\"\<last\>\""}], "]"}]}], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9129225245696907`*^9, 3.9129225245696907`*^9}},
 CellLabel->"In[63]:=",ExpressionUUID->"ab60909e-a457-4a6b-b50e-1e18760883ef"],

