Cell["\<\
By the way, if you look carefully at the screenshot, you can see that the \
package processing code itself calls a lot of specific functions - these are \
all server methods, which are defined below.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.912922623129324*^9},ExpressionUUID->"1601bcc1-d5e1-4f53-a3cf-\
fd65a53e5ccd"],

Cell["\<\
I have many more examples and thoughts I\[CloseCurlyQuote]d like to share. \
Plus I didn\[CloseCurlyQuote]t go through all the points of the comment from \
the very beginning. I know very well that the topic of programming paradigms \
and programming approaches can cause an interesting discussion, as this topic \
is loved on Hubre. I will be glad to hear the opinions of our dear readers!\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.912922632408717*^9},ExpressionUUID->"7c2abdb5-7f3e-432c-b024-\
2c435dfb36c4"],

Cell["Thank you all for your attention!", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.9129226417211394`*^9},
 FontSlant->"Italic",ExpressionUUID->"2b4e3f53-62be-4b5d-812a-a37508d9edb8"],

